<TITLE> Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain faces fourth extortion case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, June 11 (bdnews24.com)  A Comilla resident Monday filed an extortion case against former minister Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain and 11 other BNP leaders. Businessman Mohammad Ibrahim of Kolakandi village in Titas upazila filed the case with a cognisance court. Magistrate Selina Parvez asked the Titas police chief for taking legal action after a proper investigation. According to case details, Ibrahim alleged that co-accused Raja Mia and Abdul Haque demanded Tk 1 lakh from him in 2003 after they were assigned by the former health minister. He said he had paid Tk 40,000 in the first instalment and promised to pay the rest when he spoke to Mosharraf by phone. According to allegations, the accused piled pressure on Ibrahim, forcing him to leave the area for fear of life. Joint forces arrested Mosharraf at his Gulshan home in Dhaka on March 7. He faces three other extortion casesall filed with different police stations in Comilla. bdne
